0.user_question: Will was working as a sacker at a grocery store where he made 8 dollars an hour. On Monday he worked 8 hours and on Tuesday he worked 2 hours. How much money did Will make in those two days?

ost_step.2: Calculate how much Will made on Tuesday. He worked 2 hours and makes $8 per hour. So he made 2 * 8 = $16.
ost_step.3: Add how much he made on Monday to how much he made on Tuesday to get the total amount of money Will made in those two days. 64 + 16 = $80.
